{
  "apiVersion": "dashboard.grafana.app/v2alpha1",
  "kind": "Dashboard",
  "metadata": {
    "annotations": {
      "grafana.app/folder": "meraki-exporter"
    },
    "name": "meraki-client-telemetry"
  },
  "spec": {
    "annotations": [],
    "cursorSync": "Off",
    "description": "Per-client high-cardinality telemetry (signal quality, packet loss, webhook delivery) carried by the OTLP data-log channel (#622), NOT Prometheus metrics. Webhook Delivery is LIVE; Signal Quality/Packet Loss show No data pending #637 (signal_quality emission bug) - see the banner panel.",
    "editable": true,
    "elements": {
      "panel-banner": {
        "kind": "Panel",
        "spec": {
          "data": {
            "kind": "QueryGroup",
            "spec": {
              "queries": [],
              "queryOptions": {},
              "transformations": []
            }
          },
          "description": "",
          "id": 0,
          "links": [],
          "title": "\u26a0 Signal Quality / Packet Loss: No data (Webhook Delivery: LIVE)",
          "vizConfig": {
            "kind": "text",
            "spec": {
              "fieldConfig": {
                "defaults": {},
                "overrides": null
              },
              "options": {
                "content": "### Client data-log dashboard (#622) \u2014 live-verified 2026-07-03\n\n- **Webhook Delivery: LIVE** \u2705 \u2014 `meraki.org.webhook.delivery` records flow end-to-end into Loki today (OTLP data-log \u2192 collector \u2192 Loki). This tab shows real data.\n- **Signal Quality / Packet Loss: No data (pending #637)** \u2014 `meraki.wireless.client.signal_quality` + `meraki.wireless.client.packet_loss` emit zero records: signal_quality emission is coupled to the `packetLoss/byClient` response (**#637**). These two tabs light up once #637 lands (attribute names best-effort until then).\n- **#638 (OTLP-logs\u2192Loki path) is RESOLVED** \u2014 proven by webhook.delivery arriving.\n\n> Loki query form: OTel attributes are **structured metadata**, so filter as `{service_name=~\"...\"} | event_name=`\u2026`` (pipeline filter), NOT inside `{}`.",
                "mode": "markdown"
              },
              "pluginVersion": ""
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "panel-pl-logs": {
        "kind": "Panel",
        "spec": {
          "data": {
            "kind": "QueryGroup",
            "spec": {
              "queries": [
                {
                  "kind": "PanelQuery",
                  "spec": {
                    "datasource": {
                      "type": "loki",
                      "uid": "${datasource}"
                    },
                    "hidden": false,
                    "query": {
                      "kind": "loki",
                      "spec": {
                        "editorMode": "code",
                        "expr": "{service_name=~\"meraki-dashboard-exporter.*\"} | event_name=`meraki.wireless.client.packet_loss`",
                        "maxLines": 200,
                        "queryType": "range"
                      }
                    },
                    "refId": "A"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "queryOptions": {},
              "transformations": []
            }
          },
          "description": "Raw per-client packet-loss data-log lines for debugging/verifying the parser assumption once records start flowing.\n\nSchema note: OTel attributes land as Loki structured metadata (dot -> underscore, e.g. event.name -> event_name), filtered via a pipeline label filter after the selector - no logfmt/json parser stage - e.g. `{service_name=~\"...\"} | event_name=\"meraki.org.webhook.delivery\"`. LIVE-VERIFIED for meraki.org.webhook.delivery (flowing today); the equivalent field names for the two wireless-client events are ASSUMED by the same dot->underscore convention since zero records exist yet (blocked on #637) - re-verify once #637 lands.",
          "id": 7,
          "links": [],
          "title": "Raw packet-loss records (debug)",
          "vizConfig": {
            "kind": "logs",
            "spec": {
              "fieldConfig": {
                "defaults": {},
                "overrides": null
              },
              "options": {
                "dedupStrategy": "none",
                "enableLogDetails": true,
                "prettifyLogMessage": false,
                "showCommonLabels": false,
                "showLabels": false,
                "showTime": true,
                "sortOrder": "Descending",
                "wrapLogMessage": true
              },
              "pluginVersion": ""
            }
          }
        }
      },
